 monoid M if and only if E is (i)\ncoherent, (ii) noetherian, and (iii) has a surjective coherent point. This\ntopos-theoretic consideration is related to the logical and geometric problems\nconcerning Eilenberg's theory that we addressed at LICS'16, which remain open\nin this paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Dec 2015 16:21:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Dec 2015 17:25:55 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 20 Jun 2016 12:22:22 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 20 Jan 2017 08:32:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-23"}
